(162, 1, '2015-08-15 01:02:26', '2015-08-15 01:02:26', 'http://www.business.gov.au/grants-and-assistance/Pages/default.aspx\n\n&nbsp;\n\n******************************\n\nGrants and Assistance to Exporters:\n\nThe programmes are designed to help Australian businesses of all sizes and industries improve productivity and competitiveness, and create jobs.\n\nThe programmes include incentives for research and development, support for small businesses, tax and duty concessions, and assistance for industries in transition. They support invention and technology development in businesses by fostering collaboration between industry and researchers.\n\nEXPORTERS:\n\nFinancial assistance available from the federal government includes:\n\n*Austrade - help for your business to suceed in international trade and investment.\n\n*Export Concessions: Duty Drawback Scheme - obtain a refund for customs duty paid on imported goods that are subsequently exported.\n\n*Tradex - an alternative to Duty Drawbacks. A cashflow benefit for importers who intend to export goods do not have to pay the relevant customs duty or Goods and Services Tax at the time of import.\n\n*Export Market Development Grant - reimbursement for some marketing expenses.\n\n*Women in Global Business - support for women achieving international business success.\n\n*Export Finance and Insurance Corporation (EFIC) - provides finance and insurance solutions to help Australian exporters overcome financial barriers when growing their business overseas.\n\nVisit the EFIC website for more information or contact EFIC on 1800 093 724.\n\n*http://www.efic.gov.au\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFinancial assistance for exporters in your state or territory.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n*Australian Capital Territory:\n\nACT Government Exporting - information for businesses looking to export from the ACT.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n*New South Wales:\n\nThe NSW Department of Trade and Investment offers a number ofassistance programs and services to NSW exporters.\n\n*Northern Territory:\n\nTrade Support Scheme (TSS) - Under TSS, companies and business entities may apply for financial assistance to offset the international marketing costs of specific trade projects which will deliver identified trade outcomes.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n*Queensland:\n\nTrade and Investment Queensland - The Qld Government offers a comprehensive range of export assistance to support exporters and assistance in sourcing grants &amp; funding.\n\n*South Australia:\n\nExporting - The South Australian Department of State Development provides assistance and services to local companies exporting overseas. This includes market intelligence, in-market support and direct financial assistance to promote exports.\n\n*Tasmania:\n\nMarketing Assistance Scheme - assistance with developing and implementing international marketing plans.\n\n*Victoria:\n\nBusiness Victoria Export Grants - Services and programs available to Victorian exporters.\n\n*Western Australia:\n\nBusiness Grants -The Small Business WA site lists a range of grants and programs available to exporting businesses in Western Australia.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nGrants Finder:\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe Grant Finder helps you locate the grants and assistance programs most relevant to your business for free!\n\n&nbsp;\n\nGrants and other funding programs are available for businesses from the Australian, state and territory governments, and in some cases from local councils. You can search through a wide variety of grants in many categories, including developing your business, innovation and education.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nNB: Please use this link below to find your relevant Grant;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nhttp://www.business.gov.au/grants-and-assistance/grant-finder/Pages/default.aspx', 'Export Assistance & Grants', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '160-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-08-15 01:02:26', '2015-08-15 01:02:26', '', 160, 'http://trueaussiebrands.com/160-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
